==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Catel
<hw>Cat"el</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Chattel</er>.]</ety> <def>Property; -- often used by Chaucer in
contrast with <xex>rent</xex>, or <xex>income</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>⟦ldquo⟧<qex>For loss of catel</qex> may recovered be,⟦br⟧
But loss of tyme shendeth us,⟦rdquo⟧ quod he.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Catelectrode</ent>⟦br⟧
